<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en"></html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Portfolio</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
 <article>defines an article</article>
 <aside>defines an aside</aside>
 <cite>defines a citation</cite>
 <code>defines computer code</code>
 <del>defines deleted text</del>
 <em>defines emphasized text</em>
 <ins>defines inserted text</ins>
 <mark>defines marked text</mark>
 <abbr>defines an abbreviation</abbr>
 <address>defines contact information for the author/owner of a document</address>
 <bdo>defines the text direction</bdo>
 <blockquote>defines a section that is quoted from another source</blockquote>
 <q>defines a short quotation</q>
 <s>defines text that is no longer correct</s>
 <samp>defines sample output from a computer program</samp>
 <small>defines smaller text</small>
 <strong>defines important text</strong>
 <sub>defines subscripted text</sub>
 <sup>defines superscripted text</sup>
 <param>defines a parameter for an object</param>
 <source>defines multiple media resources for media elements (<video> and <audio>)</source>
 <track>defines text tracks for media elements (<video> and <audio>)</track>
 <wbr>defines a possible line-break</wbr>
 <progress>defines the progress of a task</progress>
 <meter>defines a scalar measurement within a known range (a gauge)</meter>
 <svg>defines a container for SVG graphics</svg>
 <math>defines a container for mathematical expressions</math>
 <var>defines a variable</var>
 <time>defines a specific time (or datetime)</time>
 <theader>defines a header for a document or section</theader>
 <footer>defines a footer for a document or section</footer>
 <canvas>defines a canvas for graphics</canvas>
 <details>defines additional details that the user can view or hide</details>
 <summary>defines a visible heading for a <details> element</summary>
 <colgroup>defines a group of one or more columns in a table for formatting</colgroup>
 <col>defines a column within a table</col>
 <dfn>defines a definition term</dfn>
 <figcaption>defines a caption for a <figure> element</figcaption>
 <figure>defines self-contained content, like illustrations, diagrams, photos, code listings, etc.</figure>
 <fencedframe>defines a fenced frame</fencedframe>
 <fencedframeset>defines a fenced frameset</fencedframeset>



</body>
</html>